cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with image alignment, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a deep learning-based approach to tackle the problem of across unseen modalities. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions deep learning techniques such as domain adaptation, feature transferring, and fine-tuning, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The proposed approach is an end-to-end deep convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method in image alignment, which is a multimedia problem, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
